Dang, you're fast.<br /><br />Yes, I2C is a serial connection.<br /><br />Ideally, your cart does the address decoding and puts the enable signal on one of the lines from the center of the 72-pin connector to the expansion port But if you go the expansion port route, you forgo compatibility with the Famicom and the top-loading NES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Sep 23, 2010 1:59 pm</p><hr />
