<title type="html"><![CDATA[Transferring data from Cart-&gt;Cart?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6971&amp;p=67761#p67761"><![CDATA[
So you want an external memory card that your own game can read and write, so that players can trade doodles or pokeymans or whatever between Game Paks. There are two ways to do this: either an I2C flash connected to the expansion port, or an I2C flash inside a dongle on controller port 2.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Sep 23, 2010 1:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
